Gianfilippo,

The problem is only in how the initial estimate for the solution is  
computed in module CounterFlame.py.

If you specify a multicomponent transport model, then method  
&#39;getMixDiffCoeffs&#39; (i.e. &#39;get mixture-averaged diffusion coefficients&#39;)  
generates the error you are seeing, since the multicomponent model only  
knows how to generate multicomponent diffusion coefficients. The only  
problem is that CounterFlame.py uses the diffusion coefficient of  
oxygen in forming the initial estimate.  All you need to do is to edit  
CounterFlame.py, and on line 110, replace diff[iox] with an estimate of  
the oxygen diffusion coefficient computed some other way (accuracy is  
not needed).  I will fix this in the next release...

Dave


